# Evolutionary Architecture

"Guided, incremental change as a first principle across multiple dimensions." — Ford, Parsons, Kua

## Three Pillars
1. **Incremental Change** — deployment pipelines + feature toggles
2. **Fitness Functions** — automated tests that verify architectural goals
3. **Appropriate Coupling** — quantum boundaries + team alignment

## Fitness Function Types

| Type | Scope | When | Example |
|---|---|---|---|
| Atomic | Single component | Unit test | "No package > 20 classes" |
| Holistic | Whole system | Integration | "P95 latency < 200ms" |
| Triggered | On event | Pre-commit/PR | "No circular dependencies" |
| Continuous | Ongoing | Production | "Error rate < 0.1%" |

## Strangler Fig Pattern

```
Phase 1: Route    → All traffic via Facade → Legacy
Phase 2: Extract  → Facade routes new features to New Service
Phase 3: Strangle → Legacy removed, New Service handles all
```
Routing strategies: URL-based, feature flag, canary (5%→legacy), data-based (new users → new).

## Architectural Dimensions
Per dimension: measure current → define target → write fitness function
- Technical: tech stack, data storage, communication
- Business: features, domain model, regulations
- Operational: scalability, performance, security

## Conway's Law
Team structure → Architecture shape. Fix misalignment by aligning team boundaries to Bounded Contexts.

## Anti-Patterns
- Fitness function theater: tests that never fail → make them fail intentionally to verify
- Ignoring failures: PR merges despite fitness failure → block merge
- Too many dimensions: >5 fitness functions initially → start with 3
- Premature extraction: microservices at 3-person startup → monolith first

## Checklist
- [ ] 3-5 critical dimensions identified
- [ ] Fitness function per dimension in CI/CD
- [ ] Coupling level chosen (monolith → modular → microservices)
- [ ] Team boundaries match architecture boundaries
- [ ] ADRs for each evolutionary step

## Ecosystem
- `c4-model` → C4 shows current arch; fitness functions verify it stays correct
- `ddd-core` → Bounded Contexts = natural architectural quantum boundaries
- `architecture-decision-records` → ADRs document why for each evolutionary step
- `dora-core` → DF + Lead Time = velocity of incremental change
